[b][size=150]Compatibility[/size][/b]
Tested and working on Firefox Stable/Dev. Edition, SeaMonkey and Palemoon.
[b][color=#FF0000]Not compatible with Nightly nor Windows Vista[/color][/b]

[b][size=150]Usage[/size][/b]
[list]
[*] After installed, click the button. The [b]Preference Switcher[/b] options window will appear.
[*] Set the name of the preference that you want to control/switch and save the changes.
[*] Done.[/list]

[b][size=150]Features[/size][/b]
[list]
[*] All options/settings for this button are changed without the need to edit the button.
[*] The button is updated (its image and tooltip) even if the preference that it controls is changed from any other place in the application.
[*] A custom code can be set to be executed every time the preference is switched.
[*] If the preference you wish to control/switch doesn't exists or is locked, you will be asked to create it or to unlock it on the fly.
[*] A hotkey can be set to switch the preference.
[/list]

[b][size=150]Button clicks[/size][/b]
[list]
[*] [b]Left click:[/b] Switch preference.
[*] [b]Shift + Left click:[/b] Switch preference (Inverse).
[*] [b]Middle click[/b] or [b]Control/Command + Left click:[/b] Set preference prompt.
[*] [b]Control/Command + Right click:[/b] Reset preference.
[*] [b]Control/Command + Shift + Right click:[/b] Button options.[/list]

